# TaskFlow Frontend Rules - React/TypeScript/Tailwind

## Project Overview
TaskFlow Client adalah frontend untuk sistem manajemen proyek dan maintenance pabrik thermoforming.
- **Stack**: React 18, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, React Router, Axios
- **Bahasa UI**: Indonesian (Bahasa Indonesia)
- **Bahasa Code**: English (comments, variables, functions)

---

## File Structure & Naming

### Directory Structure
```
src/
├── components/        # Reusable UI components
│   ├── ui/           # Base UI elements (Button, Modal, Input)
│   └── forms/        # Form-specific components
├── pages/            # Page/route components
├── context/          # React context providers
├── services/         # API services
│   └── api.ts        # Centralized API calls
├── types/            # TypeScript interfaces
│   └── index.ts      # Shared types
├── utils/            # Utility functions
└── App.tsx           # Main app with routing
```

### Naming Conventions
- **Components**: PascalCase (`UserProfile.tsx`, `WorkOrderCard.tsx`)
- **Utilities**: camelCase (`formatDate.ts`, `parseUtils.ts`)
- **Types**: PascalCase for interfaces, camelCase for type aliases
- **Constants**: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
- **Event handlers**: `handle{Event}` (e.g., `handleClick`, `handleSubmit`)
- **Boolean variables**: `is{State}`, `has{State}`, `should{State}`

---

## TypeScript Standards

### Interface Definitions
```typescript
// ✅ Good - Explicit interface with clear types
interface User {
  id: number;
  name: string;
  email: string;
  role: 'admin' | 'manager' | 'technician' | 'operator';
  created_at: string;
}

// ❌ Bad - Using any
interface User {
  id: any;
  data: any;
}
```

### Component Props
```typescript
// ✅ Good - Props interface with explicit types
interface CardProps {
  title: string;
  description?: string;
  status: 'active' | 'inactive';
  onAction: (id: number) => void;
  children?: React.ReactNode;
}

export default function Card({ title, description, status, onAction, children }: CardProps) {
  // ...
}
```

---

## Theme System (Light & Dark Mode)

### Using Theme Context
```typescript
import { useTheme } from '../context/ThemeContext';

export default function MyComponent() {
  const { isDark } = useTheme();
  
  return (
    <div className={isDark ? 'bg-dark-800' : 'bg-white'}>
      {/* content */}
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Color Palette - ALWAYS Use Both Modes

#### Backgrounds
```typescript
// Page background
className={isDark ? 'bg-dark-900' : 'bg-gray-50'}

// Card/Container background
className={isDark ? 'bg-dark-800' : 'bg-white'}

// Secondary/Muted background
className={isDark ? 'bg-dark-700' : 'bg-gray-100'}

// Hover states
className={isDark ? 'hover:bg-dark-700' : 'hover:bg-gray-50'}
```

